1347 DIAMETER_avp::operator=(const DIAMETER_avp& obj)
1348 {
1349  if (this != &obj)
1350  {
1351  _code = obj._code;
1352  _flags = obj._flags;
1353  _vendor = obj._vendor;
1354  _value = obj._value;
1355  _group_avp = obj._group_avp;
1356  }
1357  return *this;
1358 
1359 }
1360 DIAMETER_avp::~DIAMETER_avp()
1361 {
1362  _group_avp.clear();
1363 }
1364 CBBByteArray
1365 DIAMETER_avp::encode_binary()
1366 {
1367  CBBByteArray retval;
1368  unsigned int flags_length;
1369  unsigned int type = getAvpTypeFromCode(_code, _vendor);
1370 
1371  if (_group_avp.size() > 0)
1372  {
1373  _value = CBBByteArray();
1374 
1375  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _group_avp.size(); i++)
1376  {
1377  DIAMETER_avp gavp = _group_avp[i];
1378  CBBByteArray gavp_value = gavp.encode_binary();
1379  if (gavp_value.GetSize() > 0)
1380  {
1381  _value += gavp_value;
1382  if ((gavp_value.GetSize() % 4) > 0)
1383  {
1384  int padding = (4 - (gavp_value.GetSize() % 4));
1385  while (padding > 0)
1386  {
1387  _value += (CBBByte)0;
1388  padding--;
1389  }
1390  }
1391  }
1392  }
1393  }
1394 
1395  if (type == AVP_TYPE_NTP)
1396  {
1397  int offset = 0;
1398  if (_value.GetSize() > 0)
1399  {
1400  CBBString svalue = getValueAsString();
1401  offset = strtol(svalue.data(),(char **)0,10);
1402  }
1403  _value = getTimeValue(offset);
1404  }
1405 
1406  // Filter default values
1407  if ((_value.GetSize() == 0) && (_code != AVP_NAME_REQUESTED_SERVICE_UNIT))
1408  {
1409  return retval;
1410  }
1411 
1412  switch (_code)
1413  {
1414  case AVP_NAME_REDIRECT_SERVER_ADDRESS :
1415  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_GGSN_ADDRESS :
1416  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_PDP_ADDRESS :
1417  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_SGSN_ADDRESS :
1418  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_SMSC_ADDRESS :
1419  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_SERVED_PARTY_IP_ADDRESS :
1420  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_NEIGHBOR_NODE_ADDRESS :
1421  case AVP_NAME_HOST_IP_ADDRESS :
1422  {
1423  CBBString ip_address_s = getValueAsString();
1424  bool ipv6 = false;
1425  std::string::size_type idx = ip_address_s.find(":");
1426  if (idx != std::string::npos)
1427  {
1428  _value = CBBByteArray ();
1429  _value += (unsigned char)0;
1430  _value += (unsigned char)2;
1431  _value += colon_i(ip_address_s);
1432  }
1433  else
1434  {
1435  unsigned int ip_address_l = dd_i(ip_address_s);
1436  _value = CBBByteArray ();
1437  _value += (unsigned char)0;
1438  _value += (unsigned char)1;
1439  _value += (unsigned char)((ip_address_l >> 24) & 0xff);
1440  _value += (unsigned char)((ip_address_l >> 16) & 0xff);
1441  _value += (unsigned char)((ip_address_l >> 8) & 0xff);
1442  _value += (unsigned char)((ip_address_l >> 0) & 0xff);
1443  }
1444  }
1445  break;
1446  case AVP_NAME_TGPP_ORIGINATING_SCCP_ADDRESS :
1447  {
1448  unsigned long long signed_value;
1449  unsigned long long value = strtoull(getValueAsString().data(),(char **)0,16);
1450  //unsigned long long network_value = (long long)(htonll(signed_value));
1451  _value = CBBByteArray();
1452  _value += (unsigned char)0;
1453  _value += (unsigned char)8;
1454  int shift_value = 56;
1455  while ((((signed_value >> shift_value) & 0xff) == 0) &&
1456  (shift_value >= 0))
1457  {
1458  shift_value -= 8;
1459  }
1460  while (shift_value >= 0)
1461  {
1462  _value += (unsigned char)((signed_value >> shift_value) & 0xff);
1463  shift_value -= 8;
1464  }
1465  }
1466  break;
1467  case AVP_NAME_CC_SERVICE_SPECIFIC_UNITS :
1468  case AVP_NAME_TARIFF_CHANGE_USAGE :
1469  case AVP_NAME_CURRENCY_CODE :
1470  case AVP_NAME_VALUE_DIGITS :
1471  case AVP_NAME_EXPONENT :
1472  case AVP_NAME_CC_INPUT_OCTETS :
1473  case AVP_NAME_CC_OUTPUT_OCTETS :
1474  case AVP_NAME_CC_TIME :
1475  //TEMP TEMP TEMP case AVP_NAME_CC_TOTAL_OCTETS :
1476  case AVP_NAME_VALIDITY_TIME :
1477  case AVP_NAME_REDIRECT_MAX_CACHE_TIME :
1478  case AVP_NAME_SERVICE_IDENTIFIER :
1479  {
1480  // workaround for AVPs that have non-zero size but zero values
1481  bool all_zero = true;
1482  for (int j = 0; j < _value.GetSize(); j++)
1483  {
1484  if (_value[j] != (unsigned char)0) all_zero = false;
1485  }
1486  if (all_zero == true)
1487  {
1488  return retval;
1489  }
1490  }
1491  break;
1492  default :
1493  break;
1494  }
1495 
1496  // Filter other unused AVPs based on default values
1497  switch (type)
1498  {
1499  case AVP_TYPE_INT_32 :
1500  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_32 :
1501  {
1502  unsigned int temp_value = getValueAsInt();
1503  if (temp_value == AVP_TYPE_UNUSED_INT32)
1504  {
1505  return retval;
1506  }
1507  }
1508  case AVP_TYPE_INT_64 :
1509  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_64 :
1510  {
1511  unsigned long long temp_value = getValueAsLongLong();
1512  if (temp_value == AVP_TYPE_UNUSED_INT64)
1513  {
1514  return retval;
1515  }
1516  }
1517  default :
1518  {
1519  }
1520  break;
1521  }
1522 
1523  flags_length = _value.GetSize();
1524  bool mandatory = getAvpMandatoryFromCode(_code,_vendor);
1525 
1526  if (_vendor != 0)
1527  {
1528  diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t hdr;
1529  flags_length += sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t);
1530  flags_length |= _avp_flags_vendor;
1531 
1532  if (mandatory == true)
1533  {
1534  flags_length |= _avp_flags_mandatory;
1535  }
1536  hdr._code = htonl(_code);
1537  hdr._flags_length = htonl(flags_length);
1538  hdr._vendor = htonl(_vendor);
1539  retval += CBBByteArray ((char *)&hdr,sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t));
1540  }
1541  else
1542  {
1543  diameter_avp_hdr_t hdr;
1544  flags_length += sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t);
1545  if (mandatory == true)
1546  {
1547  flags_length |= _avp_flags_mandatory;
1548  }
1549  hdr._code = htonl(_code);
1550  hdr._flags_length = htonl(flags_length);
1551  retval += CBBByteArray ((char *)&hdr,sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t));
1552  }
1553 
1554  retval += _value;
1555  return retval;
1556 }
1557 int
1558 DIAMETER_avp::decode_binary (CBBByteArray &packet)
1559 {
1560  int retval = 0;
1561  diameter_avp_hdr_t hdr;
1562 
1563  if (packet.GetSize() < sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t)) return retval;
1564 
1565  memcpy ((char *)&hdr,packet.GetData(),sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t));
1566  unsigned int length = 0;
1567  unsigned int flags_length = ntohl(hdr._flags_length);
1568  if ((flags_length & _avp_flags_vendor) != 0)
1569  {
1570  diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t v_hdr;
1571 
1572  if (packet.GetSize() < sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t)) return retval;
1573 
1574  memcpy ((char *)&v_hdr,packet.GetData(),sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t));
1575  CBBByteArray jnk = packet.Extract(sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t));
1576  flags_length = ntohl(v_hdr._flags_length);
1577  _flags = (flags_length >> 24) & 0xff;
1578  _code = ntohl(v_hdr._code);
1579  _vendor = ntohl(v_hdr._vendor);
1580  length = flags_length & 0xffffff;
1581  retval = length;
1582  length -= sizeof(diameter_vendor_avp_hdr_t);
1583  }
1584  else
1585  {
1586  CBBByteArray jnk = packet.Extract(sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t));
1587  _code = ntohl(hdr._code);
1588  _flags = (flags_length >> 24) & 0xff;
1589  length = flags_length & 0xffffff;
1590  retval = length;
1591  length -= sizeof(diameter_avp_hdr_t);
1592  }
1593  if (length > (unsigned int)(packet.GetSize()))
1594  {
1595  retval = 0;
1596  return retval;
1597  }
1598  unsigned int type = getAvpTypeFromCode(_code, _vendor);
1599  _value = packet.Extract(length);
1600  if (type == AVP_TYPE_GROUPED)
1601  {
1602  bool recursion = true;
1603 
1604  while(recursion == true)
1605  {
1606  DIAMETER_avp group_avp;
1607  int reduce = group_avp.decode_binary(_value);
1608  if (reduce > 0)
1609  {
1610  setAvp(group_avp);
1611  CBBByteArray recurse_jnk = _value.Extract(reduce);
1612  }
1613  else
1614  {
1615  recursion = false;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  }
1619  return retval;
1620 }
1621 
1622 CBBString DIAMETER_avp::encode_string()
1623 {
1624  const CBBString start_tag("<avp>");
1625  const CBBString stop_tag("</avp>");
1626  const CBBString name_start_tag("<name>");
1627  const CBBString name_stop_tag("</name>");
1628  const CBBString value_start_tag("<value>");
1629  const CBBString value_stop_tag("</value>");
1630  CBBString name = getAvpNameFromCode(_code, _vendor);
1631  CBBString retval;
1632 
1633  if (name.length() > 0)
1634  {
1635  retval += start_tag;
1636  retval += "\n";
1637  retval += name_start_tag;
1638  retval += name;
1639  retval += name_stop_tag;
1640  retval += "\n";
1641  if (_group_avp.size() > 0)
1642  {
1643  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _group_avp.size(); i++)
1644  {
1645  retval += _group_avp[i].encode_string();
1646  }
1647  }
1648  else
1649  {
1650  retval += value_start_tag;
1651  unsigned int type = getAvpTypeFromCode(_code,_vendor);
1652  switch (type)
1653  {
1654  case AVP_TYPE_BYTES :
1655  {
1656  retval += _value.AsHexString();
1657  }
1658  break;
1659  case AVP_TYPE_STRING :
1660  {
1661  CBBString string_value((char *)_value.GetData(),_value.GetSize());
1662  retval += string_value;
1663  }
1664  break;
1665  case AVP_TYPE_INT_64 :
1666  case AVP_TYPE_INT_32 :
1667  {
1668  char cmd[256];
1669  long long signed_value = 0LL;
1670  for (int k = 0; k < _value.GetSize(); k++)
1671  {
1672  long long tmp_value = (long long)(_value[k]);
1673  signed_value <<= 8;
1674  signed_value |= tmp_value;
1675  }
1676  sprintf (cmd,"%lld",signed_value);
1677  retval += CBBString(cmd);
1678  }
1679  break;
1680  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_64 :
1681  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_32 :
1682  {
1683  char cmd[256];
1684  unsigned long long signed_value = 0LL;
1685  for (int k = 0; k < _value.GetSize(); k++)
1686  {
1687  unsigned long long tmp_value = (unsigned long long)(_value[k]);
1688  signed_value <<= 8;
1689  signed_value |= tmp_value;
1690  }
1691  sprintf (cmd,"0x%llx",signed_value);
1692  retval += CBBString(cmd);
1693  }
1694  break;
1695  default :
1696  case AVP_TYPE_NTP :
1697  case AVP_TYPE_FLOAT_32 :
1698  case AVP_TYPE_GROUPED :
1699  {
1700  }
1701  break;
1702  }
1703  retval += value_stop_tag;
1704  retval += "\n";
1705  }
1706  retval += stop_tag;
1707  retval += "\n";
1708  }
1709  return retval;
1710 }
1711 
1712 int DIAMETER_avp::decode_string(char *osp, int offset, int length)
1713 {
1714  const CBBString comment_start_tag("<!--");
1715  const CBBString comment_stop_tag("-->");
1716  const CBBString start_tag("<avp>");
1717  const CBBString stop_tag("</avp>");
1718  const CBBString name_start_tag("<name>");
1719  const CBBString name_stop_tag("</name>");
1720  const CBBString value_start_tag("<value>");
1721  const CBBString value_stop_tag("</value>");
1722  const CBBString hex_base("0x");
1723 
1724  char *sp = osp;
1725  int retval = 0;
1726 
1727  // <avp>
1728  // <name>name</name>
1729  // <value>value</value>
1730  // </avp>
1731  //
1732  // or
1733  // <avp>
1734  // <name>name</name>
1735  // <avp>
1736 
1737  char *name_start = (char *)0;
1738  char *name_end = (char *)0;
1739  char *value_start = (char *)0;
1740  char *value_end = (char *)0;
1741  bool in_comment_tag = false;
1742  bool in_name_tag = false;
1743  bool in_value_tag = false;
1744  bool in_avp_tag = false;
1745  bool in_stop_tag = false;
1746  // keep going as long as we can parse the </avp> end tag
1747  while (((offset + retval + (int)(stop_tag.length())) < length) &&
1748  (in_stop_tag == false))
1749  {
1750  if (strncmp(sp,start_tag.data(),start_tag.length()) == 0)
1751  {
1752  // if this is our not our start tag, it is a group start
1753  if (in_avp_tag == true)
1754  {
1755  DIAMETER_avp gavp;
1756  int gavp_retval = gavp.decode_string(sp,offset+retval,length);
1757  if (gavp_retval != 0)
1758  {
1759  _group_avp.push_back(gavp);
1760  retval += gavp_retval;
1761  sp += gavp_retval;
1762  }
1763  else
1764  {
1765  printf ("Error on '%s'\n",sp);
1766  return 0;
1767  }
1768  }
1769  else
1770  {
1771  in_avp_tag = true;
1772  sp += start_tag.length();
1773  retval += start_tag.length();
1774  }
1775  }
1776  else if (strncmp (sp,stop_tag.data(),stop_tag.length()) == 0)
1777  {
1778  sp += stop_tag.length();
1779  retval += stop_tag.length();
1780  in_stop_tag = true;
1781  }
1782  else if (strncmp (sp,name_start_tag.data(),name_start_tag.length()) == 0)
1783  {
1784  sp += name_start_tag.length();
1785  retval += name_start_tag.length();
1786  name_start = sp;
1787  name_end = sp;
1788  in_name_tag = true;
1789  }
1790  else if (strncmp (sp,name_stop_tag.data(),name_stop_tag.length()) == 0)
1791  {
1792  sp += name_stop_tag.length();
1793  retval += name_stop_tag.length();
1794  in_name_tag = false;
1795  }
1796  else if (strncmp (sp,comment_start_tag.data(),comment_start_tag.length()) == 0)
1797  {
1798  sp += comment_start_tag.length();
1799  retval += comment_start_tag.length();
1800  in_comment_tag = true;
1801  }
1802  else if (strncmp (sp,comment_stop_tag.data(),comment_stop_tag.length()) == 0)
1803  {
1804  sp += comment_stop_tag.length();
1805  retval += comment_stop_tag.length();
1806  in_comment_tag = false;
1807  }
1808  else if (strncmp (sp,value_start_tag.data(),value_start_tag.length()) == 0)
1809  {
1810  sp += value_start_tag.length();
1811  retval += value_start_tag.length();
1812  value_start = sp;
1813  value_end = sp;
1814  in_value_tag = true;
1815  }
1816  else if (strncmp (sp,value_stop_tag.data(),value_stop_tag.length()) == 0)
1817  {
1818  sp += value_stop_tag.length();
1819  retval += value_stop_tag.length();
1820  in_value_tag = false;
1821  }
1822  else if (in_name_tag == true)
1823  {
1824  name_end++;
1825  sp++;
1826  retval++;
1827  }
1828  else if (in_value_tag == true)
1829  {
1830  value_end++;
1831  sp++;
1832  retval++;
1833  }
1834  else
1835  {
1836  sp++;
1837  retval++;
1838  }
1839  }
1840 
1841  if ((name_start != (char *)0) && (name_end != (char *)0) && (name_start != name_end))
1842  {
1843  while (name_start != name_end)
1844  {
1845  if ((*name_start != ' ') &&
1846  (*name_start != '\t') &&
1847  (*name_start != '\r') &&
1848  (*name_start != '\n'))
1849  {
1850  break;
1851  }
1852  name_start++;
1853  }
1854  while (name_end != name_start)
1855  {
1856  if ((*name_end != ' ') &&
1857  (*name_end != '\t') &&
1858  (*name_end != '\r') &&
1859  (*name_end != '<') &&
1860  (*name_end != '\n'))
1861  {
1862  name_end++;
1863  break;
1864  }
1865  name_end--;
1866  }
1867  if (name_start == name_end) name_end++; // single character
1868  CBBString nameString = CBBString(name_start,name_end - name_start);
1869  unsigned int code = getAvpCodeFromName(nameString);
1870  unsigned int vendor = getAvpVendorFromName(nameString);
1871  if (code == 0)
1872  {
1873  printf ("getAvpVendorFromName returns 0 for '%s'\n",nameString.data());
1874  return 0;
1875  }
1876  _code = code;
1877  _vendor = vendor;
1878  }
1879  else
1880  {
1881  printf ("name_string error on %s\n",osp);
1882  return 0;
1883  }
1884 
1885  unsigned int type = getAvpTypeFromCode(_code,_vendor);
1886 
1887  if ((value_start != (char *)0) && (value_end != (char *)0))
1888  {
1889  while (value_start != value_end)
1890  {
1891  if ((*value_start != ' ') &&
1892  (*value_start != '\t') &&
1893  (*value_start != '\r') &&
1894  (*value_start != '\n'))
1895  {
1896  break;
1897  }
1898  value_start++;
1899  }
1900  while (value_end != value_start)
1901  {
1902  if ((*value_end != ' ') &&
1903  (*value_end != '\t') &&
1904  (*value_end != '\r') &&
1905  (*value_end != '<') &&
1906  (*value_end != '\n'))
1907  {
1908  value_end++;
1909  break;
1910  }
1911  value_end--;
1912  }
1913  if ((value_start == value_end) && (type != AVP_TYPE_STRING))value_end++; // single character
1914  CBBString valueString = CBBString(value_start,value_end - value_start);
1915 
1916  switch (type)
1917  {
1918  case AVP_TYPE_BYTES :
1919  {
1920  _value = CBBByteArray(valueString.data());
1921  }
1922  break;
1923  case AVP_TYPE_NTP :
1924  case AVP_TYPE_STRING :
1925  {
1926  _value = CBBByteArray(valueString.data(),valueString.length());
1927  }
1928  break;
1929  case AVP_TYPE_INT_32 :
1930  {
1931  int signed_value;
1932  if (strncmp(valueString.data(),hex_base.data(),hex_base.length()) == 0)
1933  {
1934  signed_value = strtol(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1935  }
1936  else
1937  {
1938  signed_value = strtol(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1939  }
1940  int network_value = htonl(signed_value);
1941  _value = CBBByteArray((char *)&network_value,sizeof(int));
1942  }
1943  break;
1944  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_32 :
1945  {
1946  unsigned int signed_value;
1947  if (strncmp(valueString.data(),hex_base.data(),hex_base.length()) == 0)
1948  {
1949  signed_value = strtoul(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1950  }
1951  else
1952  {
1953  signed_value = strtoul(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1954  }
1955  unsigned int network_value = htonl(signed_value);
1956  _value = CBBByteArray((char *)&network_value,sizeof(unsigned int));
1957  }
1958  break;
1959  case AVP_TYPE_INT_64 :
1960  {
1961  long long signed_value;
1962  if (strncmp(valueString.data(),hex_base.data(),hex_base.length()) == 0)
1963  {
1964  //signed_value = _strtoi64(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1965  unsigned long long value = strtoull(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1966 
1967  }
1968  else
1969  {
1970  // signed_value = _strtoi64(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1971  unsigned long long value = strtoull(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1972  }
1973  long long network_value = (long long)(htonll(signed_value));
1974  _value = CBBByteArray((char *)&network_value,sizeof(long long));
1975  }
1976  break;
1977  case AVP_TYPE_UINT_64 :
1978  {
1979  unsigned long long signed_value;
1980  if (strncmp(valueString.data(),hex_base.data(),hex_base.length()) == 0)
1981  {
1982  //signed_value = _strtoui64(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1983  unsigned long long value = strtoull(valueString.data(),(char **)0,16);
1984  }
1985  else
1986  {
1987  //signed_value = _strtoui64(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1988  unsigned long long value = strtoull(valueString.data(),(char **)0,10);
1989  }
1990  unsigned long long network_value = (long long)(htonll(signed_value));
1991  _value = CBBByteArray((char *)&network_value,sizeof(unsigned long long));
1992  }
1993  break;
1994  default :
1995  case AVP_TYPE_FLOAT_32 :
1996  case AVP_TYPE_GROUPED :
1997  {
1998  printf ("Unknown type for %s\n",osp);
1999  return 0;
2000  }
2001  break;
2002  }
2003  return retval;
2004  }

2027 CBBByteArray
2028 DIAMETER_avp::getTimeValue(int offset) const
2029 {
2030  // difference between UNIX base time (1-1-1970) and NTP base time (1-1-1900) in seconds
2031  const unsigned int ntp_basetime = (unsigned int)2208988800;
2032  CBBByteArray retval;
2033  unsigned int now_time = (unsigned int)(time((time_t *)0));
2034  if (offset >= 0) now_time += offset;
2035  else
2036  {
2037  unsigned int abs_time = abs(offset);
2038  now_time -= abs_time;
2039  }
2040  now_time += ntp_basetime;
2041  unsigned int network_time = htonl(now_time);
2042  retval = CBBByteArray ((char *)&network_time,sizeof(network_time));
2043  return retval;
2044 }

2233 unsigned long long
2234 DIAMETER_avp::htonll(const unsigned long long value) const
2235 {
2236  endian_ll_t u1;
2237  endian_ll_t u2;
2238  u1.ll = value;
2239  u2.c[0] = u1.c[7];
2240  u2.c[1] = u1.c[6];
2241  u2.c[2] = u1.c[5];
2242  u2.c[3] = u1.c[4];
2243  u2.c[4] = u1.c[3];
2244  u2.c[5] = u1.c[2];
2245  u2.c[6] = u1.c[1];
2246  u2.c[7] = u1.c[0];
2247  return u2.ll;
2248 }
2249 unsigned long long
2250 DIAMETER_avp::ntohll(const unsigned long long value) const
2251 {
2252  endian_ll_t u1;
2253  endian_ll_t u2;
2254  u1.ll = value;
2255  u2.c[7] = u1.c[0];
2256  u2.c[6] = u1.c[1];
2257  u2.c[5] = u1.c[2];
2258  u2.c[4] = u1.c[3];
2259  u2.c[3] = u1.c[4];
2260  u2.c[2] = u1.c[5];
2261  u2.c[1] = u1.c[6];
2262  u2.c[0] = u1.c[7];
2263  return u2.ll;
2264 }
